reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars An unexpected ending
reviews.reviewText: I always enjoy a good Jesse McDermitt story. This one involved Jesse, and Savannah, and Charity plus some of the Armstrong crew and a couple of interesting bad guys. Jesse is like a lot of us. Getting old and slowing down. Finn got to be a hero in this story also but it cost him. I liked the scene in gaspar's revenge after Jesse and Charity had rescued the two girls and the two adults from the human traffickers. Where one of the girls said to Jesse not a spy huh after watching encrypted communications that were far beyond what you would normally find on a civilian boat. Didn't like the ending so much but it does leave open the possibility of at least one good story maybe a couple as Jesse chases down Savannah.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 12, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I Smith's book but it seemed to be a little disjointed. The preceding books were not that way. Even with that I enjoyed it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Action and suspense
reviews.reviewText: An excellent read. There is suspense, action and emotional uncertainty. The ending was so unexpected I was shocked. This book is an enormous improvement on the prior 3-5 books. It’s good to have Jesse back on his island among familiar characters. It was like a journey back in time as Jesse’s character slipped so easily into the tranquil waters of Key West among the host of familiar characters. I’m on pins and needles as I wait for the next book to (hopefully) unravel the surprising end of this book.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 17, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Jesse keeps on going.
reviews.reviewText: I dare say I have read all of theses books and the only thing that bugs me is that I know nothing about a boat. Any kind of boat that is , so I'm not crazy about about all the " boating language " but I do read it cause I don't want to miss anything. I'm an 81 yr old female so I definitely lean towards Savannah's side of things. Please hurry and get the next book done so we can get Jesse back with his wife and son and of course dog.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Jesse and Charity together again to make wrong…. right!
reviews.reviewText: Jesse thinks of himself as retired but once again is called upon to help bring justice. Charity reappears to help.Together in the Bahamas they seek out the perpetrators to bring justice. However, this puts him crossways with wife Savannah which does not end well.Wayne Stinnett delivers another great read with action, intrigue displaying use of advanced technology that keeps you reading until…the end!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars You get what you expect in the latter series
reviews.reviewText: The formula is the same... Discover a problem that needs fixing, Marshall the right group from previous adventures, plan the take down and everything goes perfectly unlike some the earlier and significant tly better stories. However, the settings are still great, the harcters as fun as ever, and you always get a great geography lesson and learn a little more about boats. I always look forward to the next read even though the characters and adventures have mellowed with age.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Couldn’t put it down
reviews.reviewText: As usual, Wayne hits it out of the park. Well written and packed with excitement at every turn. Highly recommend the entire Jesse McDermitt series!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars becoming extremely tired of savannah
reviews.reviewText: Jesse McDermitt is admirable, courageous, and inspirational, he is compassionate, intelligent, and completely patriotic. He is excellent at anything & everything he does, and is always trying to be better. Jesse is a TRUE, RED, WHITE, & BLUE, AMERICAN HERO!Unfortunately, the love of his life, savannah is not. SPOILER ALERT!!!The idea that an covert operator or their superior would allow the untrained and interfering spouse to constantly interrupt, issue demands and ultimatums during the planning and execution of an extremely critical assignment is ludicrous. As well as dangerous, especially when the intrusion and disruption is during the middle of a covert mission.Personally, I am so disgusted with the egotistical, controlling, narcissistic, selfish behavior of savannah that I almost refused to buy or read this book! As it was, I stopped reading more than a few times.When is Jesse going to find his cojones and cease giving in to this self centered, spoiled woman? Remember, savanna has NEVER really had a job, never had to achieve anything, and thinks she is smarter and better than everyone else.One of his friends or family members must tell him! Remember, savannah lied to Jesse from the very beginning. She knew for years that Jesse was Flo's Father, and never told either one of them. She didn't allow Flo the opportunity of knowing her Daddy, even though it is a critical part of growing into a well adjusted and happy adult. savannah didn't allow Jesse to be a parent or participate in even a small part of Flo's life while she was growing up!However, as soon as Flo grows up, savanna marries Jesse, and then when Flo leaves for college, and the "empty nest syndrome" hits, luckily Jesse rescues a little orphan boy,and bingo! Adoption!Now after once again interfering into something she has no way or reference to understand, she demands Jesse save a mass murderer.When he can't without getting more people killed, including himself, and prior to hearing the entire timeline or details of what occured, savannah takes their adopted son and leaves, running and hiding from Jesse once again. she knows how and also that he will never be able to find his son! (payback for not doing EXACTLY what she demanded he do!)Once again savannah has completely shattered Jesse's heart and soul. the endI sincerely hope there is another book and in that upcoming book Jesse gets wise to the REAL savannah and moves on. Really moves on. He must exorcise her from his body, mind, soul, and heart. savannah has required complete honestly about Jesse's entire life and demanded intimate and complete details of every single event, dream or thought he has had during his life. savannah has NEVER been completely honest and truthful about everything in her life. She has prevaricated, omitted events, and lied by ommission. Nevertheless, savannah is once again demanding outcomes that are totally unachievable as well as being horrifically dangerous for Jesse, and his partner on this mission as well as extraordinarily hazardous for many others throughout the entire worldWayne, please bring back the REAL JESSE MCDERMITT! AMERICA (as well as your readers) and the entire world still need Jesse. THE REAL JESSE MCDERMITT!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on April 30, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Enjoyed this book as much as all the others in the series. Will be interesting to see where the main character goes as he grows older

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United Kingdom on March 2, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Yet another very enjoyable book from Wayne Stinnett. As always, I download on the day of publication and spend the next couple of days catching up on the adventures of Jesse and the gang. This, like it's 24 predecessors, does not disappoint.
